					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-2210380#post-2796899</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-2210380/mystery-skipper-theater-3000#post-2796899</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 21 Apr 2017 03:01:15 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Hercules Rockefeller</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2314402</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>This is great! I laughed a lot, especially at this line:</p> <blockquote> <p>KONDRAKI appears to be slightly disheveled and several butterflies are crawling on his face.</p> </blockquote> <p>That is just perfect.</p> <p>Aside from that, loved the lyrics, and using Navarro was a good choice - he's such a perfect fit for MST3K. My only criticism would be that the article was so short - I feel like more could have been done with this. For example, I wish we could have seen them riffing on a few skips/fictitious movies about skips (since riffing on stuff is the meat of MST3K), though I understand it would be hard to simultaneously describe what they're watching <em>and</em> what they're saying about it (but it could be done, IMO).</p> <p>Also, I don't know if this is intentional or not, but</p> <blockquote> <p>[ EXTRENIOUS DETAIL REDACTED ]</p> </blockquote> <p>should be <em>extraneous</em>.</p> <p>But yeah, well done. I echo Ihp's sentiment - this is an idea I definitely wish I'd had.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-2210380#post-2791885</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-2210380/mystery-skipper-theater-3000#post-2791885</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 14 Apr 2017 15:39:38 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>RJB_R</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1229263</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>It's more a matter of having MST3K on the brain&#8230; like I said, the song really did come to me in a dream. I've only seen the first episode of the return so far, but it's <em>so good</em>. Jonah is great as the new host and the quips come at you so fast the laughter doesn't have to stop. As soon as I have the opportunity I'm gluing myself to a couch and binging the entire season. This is the first Netflix original that I've actually been hyped for&#8230; and now it's here.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
